body:
### Version

0.22

### On which OS did this happen?

macOS

### Reproduction Steps

Try to compile this SV code:

```
typedef struct packed {
  logic [7:0] a;
  logic [7:0] b;
} Foo;

typedef Foo Bar;

typedef union packed {
  Bar bar;
  Foo foo;
} FooBar;
```

### Expected Behavior

It should work fine. I tried it in VCS with some extra asserts and it compiles:

```
module StaticAssert;
  if ($bits(Foo) != 16)
    $error("Foo is not the right length");
  if ($bits(Bar) != 16)
    $error("Bar is not the right length");
  if ($bits(FooBar) != 16)
    $error("FooBar is not the right length");
endmodule
```

### Actual Behavior

You get this error:

    ERROR: member bar of a packed union has 1 bits, expecting 16

If you change the second `typedef` to just be a copy of the structure then it works fine.

